vg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 28, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tpd1701568145998.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tpd1701568145998.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tpd1701568145998.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tpd1701568145998\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Updates a widget's state when the data object's data is changed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">dataUpdate(data)</code></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Arguments</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">data</code></p>\n<p class=\"p\">     The data object that describes the updated data.</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Exceptions</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\">None</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Return value</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\">None</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Description</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\">The framework calls the <code class=\"ph codeph\">dataUpdate()</code> function when the data object's data is\n\t\t\tchanged. This gives the widget an opportunity to update its data-related internals. This\n\t\t\tfunction's argument describes what data is updated, such as <code class=\"ph codeph\">value</code>,\n\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">valrep</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">classes</code>, and various other types of\n\t\t\tproperties. The data argument is an object with the following properties:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104tpd1701568145998_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"tpd1701568145998__codeblock_jpc_twj_qzb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">{\n  \"prop_id\":&lt;new or updated property value&gt;,\n  \"html:prop_id\":&lt;new or updated property value&gt;,\n  \"style:prop_id\":&lt;new or updated property value&gt;,\n  \"class:class_name\":&lt;new or updated property value&gt;,\n  \"valrep\":&lt;new or updated valrep array&gt;,\n  \"value\":&lt;new or updated value&gt;,\n}\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">There is a predefined value <code class=\"ph codeph\">uniface.RESET</code> that could be used for these\n\t\t\tproperty values, that is, value1, ..., valueN.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The valrep array is formatted as:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104tpd1701568145998_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"tpd1701568145998__codeblock_fkn_xwj_qzb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\"> [\n  { value: value1, representation: rep1 },\n  ...\n  { value: valueN, representation: repN }\n ]\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Predefined property value: <code class=\"ph codeph\">uniface.RESET</code></strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\">For all properties, beside their normal value, there is a special value\n\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">uniface.RESET</code> defined. If a property has this value in the argument\n\t\t\tof <code class=\"ph codeph\">dataUpdate()</code>, it means that the value of this property should be\n\t\t\treset to its initial value. </p>\n<p class=\"p\">For example, in a dynamic server page (DSP), there is a field <code class=\"ph codeph\">MY_FIELD</code>\n\t\t\tbound with a custom widget <code class=\"ph codeph\">MyCustomWidget</code>. Its default initial value of\n\t\t\tproperty <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"style:color\"</code> can be restored by preceding it with an\n\t\t\texclamation mark (!):</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104tpd1701568145998_html_2\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"tpd1701568145998__codeblock_nxt_qgr_zzb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$fieldproperties(MY_FIELD) = \"!style:color\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">This will result in a call to the <code class=\"ph codeph\">dataUpdate</code> function of\n\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">MyCustomWidget</code>. Its data argument will be such as the\n\t\t\tfollowing:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104tpd1701568145998_html_3\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"tpd1701568145998__codeblock_krs_sgr_zzb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">{ \n  //...\n    \"style:color\":uniface.RESET,\n  //... \n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">And the <code class=\"ph codeph\">dataUpdate</code> API function of <code class=\"ph codeph\">MyCustomWidget</code> could\n\t\t\thave an implementation, such as the following:</p>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"tpd1701568145998__pre_bm4_1hr_zzb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">class MyCustomWidget {\n  //...\n  dataUpdate(data) {\n    //...\n    if (data [\"style:color\"] === uniface.RESET) {\n        data [\"style:color\"] = my_style_color_initialValue;\n    } else {\n        // Apply data [“style:color”] property to this widget.\n        //...\n    }\n    //...\n  }\n  //...\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n<p class=\"p\">For more details about exclamation mark (!) and <code class=\"ph codeph\">$fieldproperties</code>, see\n\t\t\t\t<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aud1705998763272.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aud1705998763272.html#vhb1665702558566__topic_d55112e1_d55113e1_d55114e1_d55115e1_d55116e1\">Restoring Default Property Values in DSPs</a></p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aud1705998763272.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$fieldproperties</a><p>Return or set the current widget properties of an instance of a field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hjz1705997620702.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>RESET</a><p>A predefined value for the properties of UX widgets, which is an instance of empty object, and is shown as an empty object {} in JavaScript debugger.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5445836\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5445836\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "dataUpdate Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 28, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Updates a widget's state when the data object's data is changed. dataUpdate(data) Arguments data The data object that describes the updated data. Exceptions None Return value None Description The framework calls the dataUpdate() function when the data object's data is changed. This gives the widget an opportunity to update its data-related internals. This function's argument describes what data is updated, such as value , valrep , classes , and various other types of properties. The data argument is an object with the following properties: Explain this code { \"prop_id\":<new or updated property value>, \"html:prop_id\":<new or updated property value>, \"style:prop_id\":<new or updated property value>, \"class:class_name\":<new or updated property value>, \"valrep\":<new or updated valrep array>, \"value\":<new or updated value>, } Copy There is a predefined value uniface.RESET that could be used for these property values, that is, value1, ..., valueN. The valrep array is formatted as: Explain this code [ { value: value1, representation: rep1 }, ... { value: valueN, representation: repN } ] Copy Predefined property value: uniface.RESET For all properties, beside their normal value, there is a special value uniface.RESET defined. If a property has this value in the argument of dataUpdate() , it means that the value of this property should be reset to its initial value. For example, in a dynamic server page (DSP), there is a field MY_FIELD bound with a custom widget MyCustomWidget . Its default initial value of property \"style:color\" can be restored by preceding it with an exclamation mark (!): Explain this code $fieldproperties(MY_FIELD) = \"!style:color\" Copy This will result in a call to the dataUpdate function of MyCustomWidget . Its data argument will be such as the following: Explain this code { //... \"style:color\":uniface.RESET, //... } Copy And the dataUpdate API function of MyCustomWidget could have an implementation, such as the following: class MyCustomWidget { //... dataUpdate(data) { //... if (data [\"style:color\"] === uniface.RESET) { data [\"style:color\"] = my_style_color_initialValue; } else { // Apply data [“style:color”] property to this widget. //... } //... } //... } Copy For more details about exclamation mark (!) and $fieldproperties , see Restoring Default Property Values in DSPs Related Links $fieldproperties Return or set the current widget properties of an instance of a field. RESET A predefined value for the properties of UX widgets, which is an instance of empty object, and is shown as an empty object {} in JavaScript debugger. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}